The paper deals with the problem of finding all maximal $\alpha$-gapped repeats in a word, which involves string algorithms and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category. The paper also involves combinatorial analysis and complexity theory, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely categories. Additionally, the paper involves information theory and coding theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible category. Finally, the paper does not involve machine learning or computer vision, which makes cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) a less likely category.
